body.description: PRODUCT DESCRIPTION Introducing the Dracaena CPU Liquid Cooler with a separate pump head design for efficient heat dissipation. It uses water cooling to lower temperatures, enhancing computer performance. The aluminum water block provides ample airflow space and features an ambient light effect with ARGB color technology. With 21 color options to choose from, you can customize the lighting to suit your style and create a stunning visual display within your computer tower. The ARGB lighting allows for dynamic and synchronized lighting effects, making your setup truly stand out. The micro water channel design of the water block significantly enhances the cooling row's heat dissipation area, ensuring maximum cooling efficiency. The independent pump design further improves the overall performance of the cooling system. Our product is designed with safety, preventing leaks to protect your valuable components, including the GPU, CPU, and motherboard. Experience cooling performance and aesthetics with our CPU Liquid Cooler, elevating your computing experience to new heights.

Key features High Flow Pump With a high flow water pump, the Dracaena AIO CPU Cooler enhances the efficiency of heat dissipation. The pump operates at a higher RPM of 1800 RPM±10%,higher than usual watercooling all in one pump. This allows for better cooling and improved overall system performance. Enhanced Performance The Dracaena AIO CPU Cooler delivers superior performance with its efficient cold plate and copper bottom. The proprietary pump and fans are specifically optimized for static pressure, ensuring exceptional heat transfer from the CPU. This results in better cooling efficiency and improved overall system performance. Intelligent PWM Fan The Dracaena AIO CPU Cooler includes a single PWM fan that automatically adjusts its speed based on the CPU temperature. This intelligent fan control optimizes airflow and reduces noise levels, providing an excellent cooling solution for your desktop. Remember to set the PWM mode in the BIOS settings to fully utilize this feature.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars First AIO build
reviews.reviewText: Great price, took me a long time to get it installed + booting, though most of my issues were with my case, not the cooler itself. I could not get my computer to turn on using the included fan controller, but it works well when connected directly to my motherboard. Dropped my CPU temps way more than my previous air cooler. It looks nice, takes up less space, and syncs with my asus motherboard! I’ve only been using it for a day at this point, but i’m happy so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great, not easy to install.
reviews.reviewText: I had a cooling pump begin to fail on a Ryzen 7 3700X, but I thought it was the thermal paste not making enough contact or being contaminated. Turned out the pump finally failed. This was the closest to my original, which had decent reviews. Got it overnight, to install it the next day. Great price.Installation - mounting four screws through the motherboard was not as easy as it looks. It was a bit of a struggle, but don't overtighten until all four are securely in the mounting holes.The instructions are good but very simplistic. It would be a good idea to photograph the board so you can see where all the leads go. The instructions do not match the labels for some boards.Once it's installed, turn on the CPU and check the temps - it should be between 31c - 45c. The fans are super quiet. I use this computer for my film and voice-over editing, and the slight hum from the fans is not picked up when recording. Overall I'm pleased, but mounting the pump needs a little bit of improving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lowered temps 15-20 degrees C.
reviews.reviewText: I see a lot of people complaining about the install. If you’re capable of following simple instructions and understanding what pictures mean then the install will be easy. I had it installed and running in a little less than 45 minutes. It made a dramatic difference compared to the air cooler. Idle temps on a i7-9700k were steady at 28 degrees C. Heavy gaming in 1440 like Horizon the temps never went above 55 C. Great cooler especially at a 55 dollar clip. I HIGHLY recommend it. It’s also true RGB. Lots of different color choices and a few different cycle choices. You just need a case with a button for LED control or just use your reset switch to control it. The short 3-pin PWM connector coming from the water block can be plugged into any fan header on your motherboard. No need for extensions
